messages.message:
One of our potential partners is working with the API's (all working very well and he commented on making this a much better experience then with the enterprise platform), but he did notice he was also getting an error message when using a wrong job_directory that did not make a lot of sense (non blocking):

```moved code to thread```
this is json/html again, do you know which API this was?
This the build api on aihub.instabase.com (http://aihub.instabase.com)
It looks like we’re getting a 404. Do you have the actual offending request?
No I don't have it, but I believe my contact said they got the directory path wrong in this request

Ah got it. That could cause a 404 if the incorrect directory path produces an unrecognized url. Unfortunately I don’t think there’s much we can do for this case because the user is requesting a url that doesn’t exist. I think the best thing we could offer is to add status code checks into our suggested API calling scripts to make sure the request is returning success before proceeding
